cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the task of multi-document summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of crowdsourcing for creating a benchmark corpus, which falls under the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper proposes a baseline system and evaluation protocol, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with educational topics, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
